Steps to configure Nginx to serve a React app:

1. Build your React app:
```bash
npm run build
```

2. Copy the `build` folder to your server, e.g., `/var/www/my-app`.

3. Edit the Nginx config file (e.g., `/etc/nginx/sites-available/default`):
```nginx
server {
  listen 80;
  server_name yourdomain.com;

  root /var/www/my-app;
  index index.html index.htm;

  location / {
    try_files $uri /index.html;
  }
}
```

4. Reload Nginx:
```bash
sudo systemctl reload nginx
```

